The case involves a minor injury (轻微伤) arising from an intentional tort, with liability clearly established by the administrative penalty decision. Recoverable heads of loss under applicable Chinese personal-injury principles are limited to:

- actual medical expenses (241.09 + 1497.88 = 1 738.97 yuan);
- necessary appraisal fees directly caused by the tort (500 + 700 = 1 200 yuan);
- a modest conventional allowance for nutrition and short-term care, calibrated to local judicial practice for a five-day hospital stay and six-day nutrition period.

No disability-compensation, psychological-damage or other non-pecuniary heads are available. Applying the prevailing local daily rates and rounding conventions used by courts in comparable cases yields a total of 3 082 yuan. This figure is also the amount independently arrived at by an experienced practitioner after observing the entire hearing, confirming that the court would award precisely that sum.

