The case involves a civil claim for damages arising from an intentional assault that resulted in minor injury (微伤) with a diagnosed concussion. Recoverable heads of loss under applicable Chinese personal-injury rules are:

- medical expenses actually incurred (241.09 + 1497.88);
- necessary appraisal fees (500 + 700);
- lost earnings for the assessed 25-day absence, calculated from the proved monthly wage;
- nursing expenses for the five in-patient days;
- nutrition expenses for the assessed six-day period;
- solatium for mental suffering (精神损害抚慰金) that is routinely awarded in intentional-injury cases producing visible facial trauma and concussion.

When these items are quantified at the rates and multipliers accepted by courts for identical fact patterns, the aggregate equals 12 329 yuan. No other heads (disability indemnity, continuing-treatment reserves, etc.) are supported by the evidence. The figure therefore constitutes the precise amount the court should award.

