The court accepts the unchallenged judicial appraisals fixing a 30-day lost-work period and a 7-day nutrition period. All claimed heads of loss are therefore assessed against those periods and the documentary evidence of expenditure:

- medical costs are proved at the invoiced sum of 4288.87 yuan;  
- transport costs are proved at the claimed 200 yuan;  
- lost earnings are assessed at the claimed daily rate for the appraised 30 days (6000 yuan);  
- nutrition is assessed at the claimed daily rate for the appraised 7 days (700 yuan);  
- appraisal fees are proved at 2100 yuan.

Addition of these five items yields the total award of 14478 yuan. No other heads (nursing, disability, etc.) are supported by the appraisals or the evidence.
